  ooonana ai config
  ooonana ai ask PROMPT...
  ooonana ai chat
  ooonana ai env
  ooonana ai models
  ooonana ai provider [show|set nim|set gemini]
  ooonana ai model [show|list|set MODEL|alias NAME MODEL]
  ooonana ai agents
  ooonana ai agent activity
  ooonana ai tools
  ooonana ai tool NAME [ARGS...]
  ooonana ai audit
  ooonana ai tasks
  ooonana ai task [add|done|plan] ...
  ooonana ai history
  ooonana ai sessions
  ooonana ai status
  ooonana ai ping

Examples:
  ooonana update
  ooonana search editor
  ooonana search browser
  ooonana search file-manager
  ooonana get nano
  ooonana get chromium
  ooonana get nemo
  ooonana check
  ooonana upgrade --dry-run
  ooonana fix nano --reinstall
  ooonana purge nano
  ooonana repo build --dry-run nano
  oonana
  bunana --restart

Paths:
  repos: /usr/lib/ooonana/repo, /etc/ooonana/sources.d/*.repo
  state: /var/lib/ooonana/packages
  cache: /var/cache/ooonana
USAGE
}

usage_packages() {
  cat <<'USAGE'
Package flow:
  1. ooonana update
     Sync Ooonana repo indexes into local cache.
  2. ooonana search QUERY
     Find package names and summaries.
  3. ooonana get PACKAGE
     Install package plus Ooonana dependencies.
  4. ooonana verify PACKAGE
     Check installed file list still exists.
  5. ooonana check
     Verify every installed package file manifest.

Check before install:
  ooonana show nano
  ooonana depends full-i3

Install:
  ooonana get nano
  ooonana install nano --dry-run
  ooonana files nano

Fix/removal:
  ooonana upgrade --dry-run
  ooonana upgrade nano
  ooonana fix nano --reinstall
  ooonana remove nano
  ooonana purge nano
  ooonana check
  ooonana clean

Repos:
  ooonana sources
  ooonana repo doctor
  ooonana repo add cloud https://example.test/ooonana-repo /etc/ooonana/trusted-keys/cloud.pem
  ooonana repo index --sign-key /root/ooonana-repo.key /usr/lib/ooonana/repo
  ooonana repo build nano

Only Ooonana repos are used on target OS. Alpine APKs are imported by repo build automation before install.
USAGE
}

usage_get() {
  cat <<'USAGE'
Install package:
  ooonana update
  ooonana search nano
  ooonana show nano
  ooonana get nano

Dry run:
  ooonana get nano --dry-run

What happens:
  - reads /etc/ooonana/sources.d/*.repo and /usr/lib/ooonana/repo
  - downloads/caches remote repo metadata when needed
  - resolves Ooonana package dependencies
  - verifies package archive checksums
  - unpacks package archive into /
  - records installed metadata under /var/lib/ooonana/packages

Only Ooonana repos are fetched. Target OS does not live-fetch Alpine APKs.
USAGE
}

usage_upgrade() {
  cat <<'USAGE'
Upgrade packages:
  ooonana update
  ooonana upgrade --dry-run
  ooonana upgrade
  ooonana upgrade nano

Meaning:
  - no package names: check every installed package
  - package names: upgrade only those packages
  - --dry-run: show changes, install nothing

Repair:
  ooonana fix
  ooonana fix nano --reinstall
USAGE
}

usage_remove() {
  cat <<'USAGE'
Remove packages:
  ooonana remove nano
  ooonana remove nano editor --dry-run
  ooonana remove libfoo --force

Purge packages:
  ooonana purge nano

Meaning:
  remove: run package remove hook, remove installed package files, keep config/state
  purge: remove package and Ooonana config directories for that package
  --force: ignore installed packages that still depend on the target

Check before removing:
  ooonana files nano
  ooonana verify nano
USAGE
}

usage_repo_help() {
  cat <<'USAGE'
Repo commands:
  ooonana sources
  ooonana repo doctor
  ooonana repo add NAME URI [PUBKEY]
  ooonana repo remove NAME
  ooonana repo index [--sign-key KEY] [PATH]
  ooonana repo build [options] [PACKAGE...]

Build examples:
  ooonana repo add cloud https://example.test/ooonana-repo
  ooonana repo remove cloud
  ooonana repo doctor
  OOONANA_SOURCE_ROOT=/path/to/Ooonana-OS ooonana repo build nano
  ooonana repo build --dry-run nano
  ooonana repo build --out-dir /var/tmp/ooonana-repo nano

Repo source file:
  /etc/ooonana/sources.d/cloud.repo

Source format:
  OOONANA_REPO_NAME="cloud"
  OOONANA_REPO_URI="https://github.com/Ooonana/Ooonana-OS/releases/download/packages-latest/ooonana-package-repo.tar.gz"
  OOONANA_REPO_KEY="/etc/ooonana/trusted-keys/cloud.pem"

GitHub Releases tarball source:
  OOONANA_REPO_NAME="release"
  OOONANA_REPO_URI="https://github.com/Ooonana/Ooonana-OS/releases/download/packages-latest/ooonana-package-repo.tar.gz"

Ooonana can sync direct HTTP repos or a release tarball that contains index.tsv,
SHA256SUMS, optional SHA256SUMS.sig, *.pkg files, and archives/.

Signed repos:
  ooonana repo index --sign-key /root/repo.key /srv/ooonana-repo
  ooonana repo add cloud https://example.test/ooonana-repo /etc/ooonana/trusted-keys/cloud.pem
  OOONANA_REPO_VERIFY_KEY=/etc/ooonana/trusted-keys/cloud.pem ooonana update
  OOONANA_REQUIRE_SIGNED_REPOS=1 ooonana update

Private GitHub release repos:
  OOONANA_REPO_TOKEN=github_pat_or_token ooonana update
  OOONANA_GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_or_token ooonana update
USAGE
}

